Vice President Kamala Harris and Crown Prince Salman bin Hamad Al Khalifa of Bahrain had a discussion about the situation in Gaza, focusing on protecting civilians and increasing humanitarian assistance. They also talked about stabilizing the Middle East region and preventing regional escalation. Both leaders condemned the Houthi attacks on commercial vessels in the Red Sea, emphasizing that these actions pose a threat to freedom of navigation and global trade. They mentioned the UN Security Council's condemnation statement and the formation of Operation Prosperity Guardian, an international naval coalition patrolling the Red Sea to protect maritime traffic. The Vice President reaffirmed the strong bilateral relationship between the United States and Bahrain, including cooperation on regional security, defense, intelligence, and economic ties. They also discussed expanding cooperation in commerce, science, and technology, as well as the implementation of the "Comprehensive Security Integration and Prosperity Agreement" signed last year.